stylometry: Aggregate planning is dealing with supply and demand. It allows you to choose how much of something you need to purchase and sell to make a profit. In aggregate planning you need to consider that the market can always change along with supply and demand. One day you may have a high demand for a product and then the next no one could want it. The goal of aggregate planning is to buy enough products that you will be able to sell without having alot left over. The tradeoffs that are involved are either you buy alot hoping that it will all sell and you make a large profit but at the same time you could buy alot and none of it could sell. There is always a tradeoff.
